import numpy as np

def score(item, bins):
    """Create a new algorithm that calculates the scores for the bins
    based on the difference between the remaining capacity of each bin 
    and the item size, multiplied by the logarithm of the remaining 
    capacity, then subtracts the maximum value across all bins from 
    the obtained scores, finally normalizes the scores by dividing 
    them by the sum of all scores."""

    # Calculate the differences between the remaining capacity of each bin and the item size
    differences = bins - item

    # Multiply the differences by the logarithm of the remaining capacity
    scores = differences * np.log(bins)

    # Subtract the maximum value across all bins from the scores
    scores -= np.max(scores)

    # Normalize the scores by dividing them by the sum of all scores
    scores /= np.sum(scores)

    return scores
